  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> March 20, 2026</p>

  <p>This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>Thetia</strong> ("we", "our", or "us") handles information when you use the Thetia mobile application.</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> When you sign in using Apple or Firebase Authentication, we receive a unique user identifier. We do not collect your real name or email unless explicitly provided by Apple according to your settings.</li>
    
    <li><strong>User Data:</strong> We store information related to your in-app progress, such as statistics, achievements, and gameplay-related data, in order to provide core app functionality.</li>
    
    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We may collect anonymized analytics data (e.g. app usage, interactions, performance) to improve the app experience.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
  <p>We use collected data to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide and maintain app functionality</li>
    <li>Save and sync your progress</li>
    <li>Improve performance and user experience</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Advertising (Google AdMob)</h2>
  <p>Thetia displays ads using <strong>Google AdMob</strong>. AdMob may process data such as device identifiers and advertising data to provide and measure ads.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>We use <strong>non-personalized ads</strong>, meaning ads are not based on your personal data or behavior across apps.</li>
    <li>AdMob and its partners may still collect limited data for basic ad delivery and performance.</li>
    <li>You can manage ad preferences in your device settings.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Data Storage</h2>
  <p>User data (such as account identifiers and progress) is stored securely using <strong>Firebase services</strong>. We do not sell your data or share it with third parties for marketing purposes.</p>

  <h2>5. Gameplay & Interactions</h2>
  <p>Thetia includes gameplay features such as card collection and battles. These battles are <strong>simulated</strong> and do not involve direct real-time interaction with other users.</p>

  <h2>6. Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>We do not sell or rent your personal data. Data may be processed by trusted third-party services used to operate the app, including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Firebase (authentication, database, analytics)</li>
    <li>Google AdMob (advertising)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. Children’s Privacy</h2>
  <p>Thetia is intended for users aged <strong>18 and older</strong>. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

  <h2>8. Security</h2>
  <p>We take reasonable measures to protect your data. However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure.</p>

  <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be reflected on this page with a new "Last updated" date.</p>

  <h2>10. Contact</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions, contact us at: <strong>george.ot.dev@gmail.com</strong></p>

